node.text:
Scorpios, this month makes 10 years since I first started #ScorpioMystique on Twitter, and it’s been 8 years since i’ve been writing daily scopes. i love this community and my work so deeply, so much that it doesn’t often feel like work, it feels like play! and yet, i must still rest and recalibrate, and this Cancer New Moon is the perfect time for me to make a shift 🦋 (my Mars is in Cancer, and go look at the number of posts on my page… aligned AF ✨)
.
.
starting today i’m taking a six-month break from sharing daily scopes, even on my app. this will allow me to rest and to complete writing my first astrology book which i’m so excited to share with you soon!! 😊 weekly, monthly and yearly #horoscopes will still be shared on here and my free @knowthezodiac app, so it’s all good, i’m still here, just temporarily restructuring 🌙
.
.
all the answers you seek are within you; i’m simply a guide, leading you back to yourself. i know you’ll continue to thrive beyond belief these next six months, which is why i wrote yesterday’s scope letting you know of your alchemist powers. so use these 6 months to deepen your knowledge of self and to become your own astrologer (as we all should be). i love you all deeply, and i’m so grateful for the support and loyalty of this community! 🌹
.
.
thank you for being here ♏️♥️✨ Love Always, @dossevia 🦂
